	  <h2>Course Prerequisites or Co-requisites</h2>
	  <p>To successfully complete this course, students should have the following skills:
	    <ul>
	      <li>Understanding of probability: distributions, marginalization, Bayes’ rule</li>
	      <li>Familiarity with probabilistic graphical models: Markov random fields, factor graphs, Bayes nets</li>
	      <li>At least an undergraduate level understanding of linear algebra, calculus, and some familiarity with concepts in nonlinear and discrete optimization</li>
	      <li>Advanced programming (to complete term project)</li>
	    </ul>
	  </p>

